@john - by default the DRP endpoint will respond accordingly based on the ingress interface of the DRP endpoint that packets come in - however you can override the behavior with two (complimentary) options:
• start DRP w/ `--static-ip=1.2.3.4` - to set the fallback interface address to respond from
• add `--force-static` to force the fallback to always use the Static IP assigned - and skip our algorithms

